# Forms & Validation

## Rules

- Forms: shadcn `<Form>` + `react-hook-form` + `@hookform/resolvers/zod`.
- Every form field validated via Zod — no manual validation in handlers.
- Same schema used in API route AND frontend form.

## Schema location

```
schemas/
  generic/          # Reusable primitives — import everywhere
    strings.ts      # nonEmptyString, optionalString, etc.
    numbers.ts      # positiveNumber, optionalNumber, etc.
    common.ts       # email, personName, phone, etc.
  [feature]/
    login.ts        # Composes generic validators
```

## Generic validators (reuse, don't duplicate)

```typescript
// schemas/generic/strings.ts
export const nonEmptyString = z.string().trim().min(1, 'Required')

// schemas/generic/common.ts
export const email = z.string().trim().email('Invalid email')
export const personName = nonEmptyString.min(2, 'Name too short')

// Feature schema composes generics
export const loginSchema = z.object({
  email,
  password: nonEmptyString,
})
```

## API validation

```typescript
// app/api/auth/login/route.ts
const parsed = loginSchema.safeParse(body)
if (!parsed.success) return NextResponse.json({ error: parsed.error.flatten() }, { status: 400 })
```

## Form component pattern

```typescript
const form = useForm({ resolver: zodResolver(loginSchema), defaultValues: { ... } })
// Submit via useMutation — NOT useState for loading/error
```
